## M22: safe-whitelist builtins are usable outside a `raw` block.
##
## Per GPT-5.5 entry 35 (M21 design): pure compile-time type
## queries and meta operations don't require a raw context.
## The V1 safe whitelist covers:
##
##   @sizeOf / @alignOf       - type size / alignment queries
##   @TypeOf / @typeName      - type introspection
##   @hasDecl / @hasField     - meta queries
##   @len                     - array / slice length
##   @This                    - current containing type (generics)
##
## All are pure, ownership-safe, and don't manipulate pointers.
## Adding a new safe builtin requires explicit audit per the
## runtime-comment-encoded criteria.

sub main()
  arr = [1, 2, 3]
  n = @len(arr)              # OK: @len is safe
  print(n)
